programme.title: This Place - The Journey of the Bogong Moths

programme.title: I Was Actually There - Nicky Winmar's Stand Against Racism

programme.title: Dream Gardens - Kyneton, VIC

programme.title: Ta Vie Sans Ca

programme.desc: Jacob, Emily, Nathalie and Lionel are drama students and have been selected by their teacher Marianne, to represent Guadeloupe for the West Indies-French Guiana drama competition. As Jacob and Emily begin to feel a mutual attraction, the spark between Lionel and Nathalie is rekindled.

programme.title: Zetwal Caraïbes
programme.desc: Jacob is taken aback by the revelation made by Iris, with whom he'd had a one night stand. Following her mother's death, Nathalie is in search of the father she has never known. Lionel has begun dealing in drugs again.

programme.title: Zetwal Caraïbes
programme.desc: Lionel has to face up to what his father has done, actions that could have serious consequences. Marianne is delighted by the work accomplished by the pair Jacob and Emily. Meanwhile, Nathalie is making progress in her search for her father.

programme.title: Zetwal Caraïbes
programme.desc: Putting her all into preparing for the competition, Emily is supported by Marianne in her choice of a major text from Haitian literature. Despite everything the rehearsals turn out to be a total disaster. The police are taking a close interest in Lionel and his family.

programme.title: Version FranCaise
programme.desc: At the edge of the Fontainebleau Forest, we visit a museum dedicated to the Barbizon painters. Diane Benoit du Rey paints light on canvas and light fittings. Between textile craftwork, painting and sport, the brand 3. Paradis, cultural fusion. Decorative gilder, there's gold at the tip of elisabeth Bonjean's paintbrush.

programme.title: Rassemblance
programme.desc: At 17, fleeing the Taliban, Rohullah Hossiny travels through Iran, Turkey, and Greece before arriving in Belgium. In Brussels, thanks to the Duo for a job association, he finds a mentor and joins Corica, where he becomes a master roaster. In turn, he trains other exiles.

programme.title: Le Tour De France : Une Passion FranCaise
programme.desc: Since its creation in 1903, the Tour de France has shaped the French collective memory, establishing itself as one of the country's most unifying sports events. How did it become such an intrinsic part of French life? We look back over 120 years of personal accounts and archive footage.

programme.title: Terra Artistika
programme.desc: Before becoming a painter Pierre Sojo had a passion for drawing as an art in its own right. Today his drawings also serve as preparatory sketches prior to his painting.

programme.title: Sur La Dalle
programme.desc: Adamsberg and Mathieu are sure: a serial killer is on the loose. They need to identify his motive to catch him before he can do any more harm. The key to the enigma is closely linked to regional folklore. Lying on a dolmen, Adamsberg uses his imagination to find the solution.
